Description

[edit]

This list contains links to English Wikipedia articles that don't exist.

All link styles except external links appear on this list. That includes templates like {{w}} and {{wikipedia}}, links generated within quotation templates, raw [[w:...]] link syntax, and so on.

Links to Wikipedia titles ending in the word "phonology" (as auto-generated by {{IPA}}) or "language" (as auto-generated by {{der}} and similar templates) are excluded.

Cleanup instructions

[edit]

These issues can be resolved either on the Wiktionary end (for example, by fixing typos in the link, or by removing the Wikipedia link entirely) or on the Wikipedia end (for example, by creating a redirect to a pre-existing article).

If a link occurs repeatedly, it probably appears in a template or module. You can easily search the Template or Module namespaces using a search like template:insource:"missing wikipedia article" or module:insource:"missing wikipedia article".
